<topic xml:id="ai-intro-how-works"
 role="reference" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>&productname; building blocks</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tbazant@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        &productname; is designed to run on a cluster of nodes. It consists of
        basic supportive software components and a collection of popular open
        source AI components and tools called <emphasis>&ailibrary;</emphasis>.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    Basic software components include:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&slsa;</emphasis> as the underlying operating
        system with the optional &nvidia; driver installed. If you require an
        immutable operating system, &slema; is the recommended alternative.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&kube;</emphasis> cluster&mdash;preferably
        &rke2;&mdash;managed by &ranchermanager; ensuring container and
        application lifecycle management.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&nvoperator;</emphasis> to utilize the &nvidia;
        GPU computing power and capabilities for processing AI-related tasks.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&ssecurity;</emphasis> for security and
        compliance.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&sobservability;</emphasis> providing advanced
        performance and data monitoring.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&sstorage;</emphasis> for enterprise-grade storage
        solution.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis role="bold">&svirtualization;</emphasis> for virtualized
        workloads.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    The &ailibrary; includes:
  </para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&milvus; (<link xlink:href="https://milvus.io"> https://milvus.io</link>)</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          A vector database built for generative AI applications with minimal
          performance loss.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&ollama; (<link xlink:href="https://ollama.com">https://ollama.com</link>)</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          A platform that simplifies installation and management of large
          language models (LLM) on local devices.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&certmanager; (<link xlink:href="https://cert-manager.io/">https://cert-manager.io/</link>)</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          An extensible X.509 certificate controller for &kube; workloads.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>&owui; (<link xlink:href="https://openwebui.com">https://openwebui.com</link>)</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          An extensible Web user interface for the &ollama; LLM runner.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
